solutions.content:
Just like robot clean problem, use```curDirection```to record the curDirection and ```(curDirection + 1) % 4```to find the next direction.
When the direction is equals 0 or 2, ```len++```。
```
class Solution {
    public int[][] spiralMatrixIII(int R, int C, int r0, int c0) {
        int[] dx = new int[]{0, 1, 0, -1};
        int[] dy = new int[]{1, 0, -1, 0};
        List<int[]> list = new ArrayList<>();
        int curDirection = 0;
        list.add(new int[]{r0, c0});
        int len = 0;
        while (list.size() < R * C) {
            if (curDirection == 0 || curDirection == 2) len++;
            for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
                r0 += dx[curDirection];
                c0 += dy[curDirection];
                if (r0 < 0 || r0 >= R || c0 < 0 || c0 >= C) continue;
                list.add(new int[]{r0, c0});
            }
            curDirection = (curDirection + 1) % 4;
        }
        int[][] res = new int[list.size()][2];
        for (int i = 0; i < res.length; i++) {
            res[i] = list.get(i);
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```

