solutions.content:
The key point is to traverse the elements in correct order.
### Steps:
* Find out how many times we should do the traversal (four lines one time, as shown in the graph);
* Each time, we traverse four lines, and we push every element we meet, no matter whether they belong to the matrix or not;
* We filter the result we got, and leave only elements that belong to the matrix.
![image](https://s3-lc-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/users/lmiaoj/image_1534089926.png)

```
var spiralMatrixIII = function(R, C, r0, c0) {
    let n = Math.max(r0, c0, R-1-r0, C-1-c0);
    let res = [[r0,c0]];
    for(let i=1; i<=n; i++){
    	for(let j=1-i; j<=i; j++) res.push([r0+j,c0+i]); //line 1
    	for(let j=i-1; j>=-i; j--) res.push([r0+i,c0+j]); //line 2
    	for(let j=i-1; j>=-i; j--) res.push([r0+j,c0-i]); //line 3
    	for(let j=1-i; j<=i; j++) res.push([r0-i,c0+j]); //line 4
    }
    return res.filter(x=>x[0]>=0&&x[0]<R&&x[1]>=0&&x[1]<C);
};
```

