# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The algorithm generates a spiral path by simulating movement starting from a given position. It traverses right, down, left, and up in a spiral pattern, increasing the step length to cover all cells.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Using sets, the algorithm tracks already traversed and all possible coordinates. It ensures cell validity and avoids revisiting cells. By incrementally updating the step length, it efficiently covers all cells in the grid. The output grid is constructed with the visited cells in the order of traversal, forming a spiral pattern that represents the desired path. This approach ensures a complete and optimized traversal of the grid to solve the spiral matrix III problem.
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(row^2 + column^2)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(row * column)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> spiralMatrixIII(int rows, int cols, int rStart, int cStart) {
        // Create an unordered_set to store the coordinates of all cells in the grid
        unordered_set<string> coordinates;
        for (int r = 0; r < rows; r++) {
            for (int c = 0; c < cols; c++) {
                // Convert the row and column indices to a string and insert into the set
                coordinates.insert(to_string(r) + "-" + to_string(c));
            }
        }

        // Create an unordered_set to store the already traversed coordinates
        unordered_set<string> AlreadyTraversed;

        // Create a vector to store the final output grid
        vector<vector<int>> OutputGrid;

        // Initialize the current row and column with the starting positions
        int curr_row = rStart;
        int curr_column = cStart;

        // Push the starting cell into the output grid
        OutputGrid.push_back(vector<int>{curr_row, curr_column});

        // Mark the starting cell as already traversed
        AlreadyTraversed.insert(to_string(curr_row) + "-" + to_string(curr_column));

        // Initialize the current step length to 1
        int curr = 1;

        // Continue traversing until all cells have been visited
        while (AlreadyTraversed.size() != coordinates.size()) {
            // Traverse to the right
            for (int i = 0; i < curr; i++) {
                // Move to the next right cell
                curr_column++;

                // If the cell is within the grid and not already traversed
                if (coordinates.find(to_string(curr_row) + "-" + to_string(curr_column)) != coordinates.end()) {
                    // Push it to the output array
                    OutputGrid.push_back(vector<int>{curr_row, curr_column});

                    // Mark it as already traversed
                    AlreadyTraversed.insert(to_string(curr_row) + "-" + to_string(curr_column));
                }
            }

            // Traverse down
            for (int i = 0; i < curr; i++) {
                // Move down by 1
                curr_row++;

                // If the cell is within the grid and not already traversed
                if (coordinates.find(to_string(curr_row) + "-" + to_string(curr_column)) != coordinates.end()) {
                    // Push it to the output array
                    OutputGrid.push_back(vector<int>{curr_row, curr_column});

                    // Mark it as already traversed
                    AlreadyTraversed.insert(to_string(curr_row) + "-" + to_string(curr_column));
                }
            }

            // Increment the current step length
            curr++;

            // Traverse to the left
            for (int i = 0; i < curr; i++) {
                // Move left by one
                curr_column--;

                // If the cell is within the grid and not already traversed
                if (coordinates.find(to_string(curr_row) + "-" + to_string(curr_column)) != coordinates.end()) {
                    // Push it to the output array
                    OutputGrid.push_back(vector<int>{curr_row, curr_column});

                    // Mark it as already traversed
                    AlreadyTraversed.insert(to_string(curr_row) + "-" + to_string(curr_column));
                }
            }

            // Traverse up
            for (int i = 0; i < curr; i++) {
                // Move up by 1
                curr_row--;

                // If the cell is within the grid and not already traversed
                if (coordinates.find(to_string(curr_row) + "-" + to_string(curr_column)) != coordinates.end()) {
                    // Push it to the output array
                    OutputGrid.push_back(vector<int>{curr_row, curr_column});

                    // Mark it as already traversed
                    AlreadyTraversed.insert(to_string(curr_row) + "-" + to_string(curr_column));
                }
            }

            // Increment the current step length
            curr++;
        }

        // Return the final output grid containing the spiral path
        return OutputGrid;
    }
};
```

