solutions.content:
The square we walk in grows its sides by **2** each iteration; i.e., **1 x 1**-> **3 x 3**-> **5 x 5**. The walk down needs to be one shorter than the others, and the walk right needs to be one longer.

```
class Solution {
    public int[][] spiralMatrixIII(int rows, int cols, int rStart, int cStart) {
        int[][] res = new int[rows * cols][2];

        int x = rStart, y = cStart, idx = 0, spiralSize = 1;
        while (idx < res.length) {
            //walk down
            for (int i = 0; i < spiralSize - 2; i++) {
                if (x >= 0 && y >= 0 && x < rows && y < cols)
                    res[idx++] = new int[]{x, y};
                x++;
            }
            //walk left
            for (int i = 0; i < spiralSize - 1; i++) {
                if (x >= 0 && y >= 0 && x < rows && y < cols)
                    res[idx++] = new int[]{x, y};
                y--;
            }
            //walk up
            for (int i = 0; i < spiralSize - 1; i++) {
                if (x >= 0 && y >= 0 && x < rows && y < cols)
                    res[idx++] = new int[]{x, y};
                x--;
            }
            //walk right
            for (int i = 0; i < spiralSize; i++) {
                if (x >= 0 && y >= 0 && x < rows && y < cols)
                    res[idx++] = new int[]{x, y};
                y++;
            }
            spiralSize += 2;
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```

