# Intuition
First of all, set the left and right pointer as cStart and up and down pointer as rStart.And initialize num as 0 to keep track of element we have visited.
Then do the following in the different blocks:
//Upper Block (dir=0)
    Traverse it from left to right keeping **"up"** pointer as constant and after it increment the **"right"** pointer by 1. 
//Right Block (dir=1)
    Traverse it from up to down keeping **"right"** pointer as constant and after it increment the **"down"** pointer by 1. 
//Lower Block (dir=2)
    Traverse it from right to left keeping **"down"** pointer as constant and after it decrement the **"left"** pointer by 1. 
//Left Block (dir=3)
    Traverse it from down to up keeping **"left"** pointer as constant and after it decrement the **"up"** pointer by 1.
**Note :-** Before traversing any block, check whether it(left,right,up,down) lies in the matrix or not. 
# Approach
Two pointers.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
    O(rows*cols)


# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> spiralMatrixIII(int rows, int cols, int rStart, int cStart) {
        vector<vector<int>> result(rows*cols,vector<int>(2,0));
        int left=cStart,right=cStart,up=rStart,down=rStart;
        int dir=0,num=0;
        while (num < rows*cols){
            //upper block
            if (dir==0){
                if (up>=0){
                    for (int i=max(left,0);i<=min(right,cols-1);i++){
                        result[num][0]=up;
                        result[num][1]=i;
                        num++;
                    }
                }
                right++;
            }
            //right block
            if (dir==1){
                if (right<cols){
                    for (int i=max(up,0);i<=min(down,rows-1);i++){
                        result[num][0]=i;
                        result[num][1]=right;
                        num++;
                    }
                }
                down++;
            }
            //lower block
            if (dir==2){
                if (down < rows){
                    for (int i=min(right,cols-1);i>=max(left,0);i--){
                        result[num][0]=down;
                        result[num][1]=i;
                        num++;
                    }
                }
                left--;
            }
            //left block
            if (dir==3){
                if (left>=0){
                    for (int i=min(down,rows-1);i>=max(up,0);i--){
                        result[num][0]=i;
                        result[num][1]=left;
                        num++;
                    }
                }
                up--;
            }
            dir++;
            if (dir==4)
                dir=0;
        }
        return result;
    }
};
```

