<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Number of cheeseSlices is the variable that determine how many JumboBurger and SmallBurger will be made with zero remaining for both slices

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
    First if odd number of tomatoSlices is given return [] b/c it is not possible to divide evenly.For number of cheeseSlices iterate in for loop and try every combination of i and n-i. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(n), where n is number of cheeseSlices given.

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(n)
# Code
```
/**
 * @param {number} tomatoSlices
 * @param {number} cheeseSlices
 * @return {number[]}
 */
var numOfBurgers = function(tomatoSlices, cheeseSlices) {
    if(tomatoSlices %2 != 0) return []

    const JB=4,SB=2;
    for(let i=0; i<=cheeseSlices; i++){
        if(JB*i + SB*(cheeseSlices-i) == tomatoSlices){
            return [i,cheeseSlices-i]
        }
    }

    return []

};
```

