**Intuition for Solving OFFLINE QUERIES QUESTION**
1. There will be first of all some `queries will be given`.
2. Then we should first consider of `solving a single query in the best optimized way`.
3. Then after applying the optimised approach found for a single querie in step2 , we will `apply it in every query and time complexity would be somewhat close to O(q.size() * N) because for every query we will be traversing whole array.`.
4. Now we should think about applying **offline query** and we need to observe below written type of a scenario for offline query.

  ```
```
  ```
In most of the case there would be some limit value would be given for every query.
Then we will see that:
	       For eg : <=7 will be also candidate for <=10 which will also be candidate for <=20 and so on.
If we observe above type of  scenario in any query type question. Then we simply need to apply the offline query algorithm.
```
