# Approach
- Sort the edgelist and queries arrays based on their distance and limit value
- We also need to store the relative order as we want to return the answer of our queries array in that order
- Now we will build the graph until the edge dist < limit
- Check if the queries vertices belong to the same componenet
  - If yes answer would be true for that query 
  - Else answer would be false

Here we will use Disjoint Set Union to build the graph as it would be easy to check whether two vertices belong to the same component or not.
- If they belong to the same component then we can have a path where distance of each edge path is strictly less than the limit of our query.


