# Intuition
The question is fairly easy one if Time complexity is ignored. We just need to traverse the queries array and see if there is a path possible and each edge is less than the given value in queries.
But the trick lies to solve it within the given constraints and for that we can make use of **Sorting and DSU**.


# Approach
- First thought that comes is, for each query we will take all the nodes disconnected and then using DSU we will connect it if the edge between any two nodes < queries[i][2], and at last see if there is a path from queries[i][0] till queries[i][1].
- Here the problem would be that after each query we would need to clear our DSU result and start from scratch.
- SO in order to overcome this we need to **sort**. We will sort the queries vector by the **limit** given. Since we are sorting the queries vector and we need to return the result by the index, we will add index to the queries vector then sort it so that the order is preserved.
- We will also sort the edgeList according to the dis.
- So Basically for each query, we will traverse it and we will connect all the nodes using DSU such that queries[i][2] >  edgeList[j]2]. If any node is connected for queries[i][x] then it will be connected for queries[i][y], given that y>x. That is why we are sorting both edgeList and queries according to the dis and limit value respectively.
- Thus with help of sorting we are not doing any repetitive traversal. \
- At last we are checking if the nodes are connected, if yes for that query we are storing True else False.

# Complexity
- **Time complexity**:
We are sorting both edgeList and queries vector. So TC O(nlogn)

- **Space complexity**:
We are using O(n) to store parent and rank vector for DSU.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int>parent;
    vector<int>rank;

    int findParent(int i)
    {
        if(parent[i]==i)
                return i;
        return findParent(parent[i]);
    }

    void unionx(int x,int y)
    {
        int x_parent=findParent(x);
        int y_parent=findParent(y);		

        if(x_parent==y_parent) return;
        if(rank[x_parent]>rank[y_parent])
                parent[y_parent]=x_parent;
        else if(rank[y_parent]>rank[x_parent])
                parent[x_parent]=y_parent;
        else{
            parent[x_parent]=y_parent;
            rank[y_parent]++;
        }

    }
    static bool comp(vector<int>&v1,vector<int>&v2)
    {
        return v1[2]<v2[2];
    }
    vector<bool> distanceLimitedPathsExist(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edgeList, vector<vector<int>>& queries) {
        parent.resize(n);
        rank.resize(n);

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            parent[i]=i;
            rank[i]=0;
        }

        for(int i=0;i<queries.size();i++)
        {
            queries[i].push_back(i);
        }

        sort(edgeList.begin(),edgeList.end(),comp);
        sort(queries.begin(),queries.end(),comp);

        vector<bool>result(queries.size(),false);

        int j=0;
        for(int i=0;i<queries.size();i++)
        {
            int u=queries[i][0];
            int v=queries[i][1];
            int d=queries[i][2];
            int idx=queries[i][3];

            while(j<edgeList.size() and edgeList[j][2]<d)
            {
                unionx(edgeList[j][0],edgeList[j][1]);
                j++;
            }

            if(findParent(u)==findParent(v))
                result[idx]=true;
            else
                result[idx]=false;
        }
        return result;





    }
};
```

